uses for the ASCII85 codec,
see https://mom.readthedocs.org/en/latest/api/codec.html#module-mom.codec

$ sudo pip install mom





compiled dxmain.c after
commander@zombie:~/sources/ghostpdl/gs/psi$ cp ../devices/gdevdsp.h ./
with
commander@zombie:~/sources/ghostpdl/gs/psi$ gcc `pkg-config gtk+-2.0 --cflags` -o meings dxmain.c -lgs `pkg-config gtk+-2.0 --libs`

then linked it to here:
ln -s ~/sources/ghostpdl/gs/psi/meings mgs


this both does soemthing:
(draws the image!)
commander@zombie:~/Projekte/Bücher/friedhofsengel/Tools/Multitone/Code$ ./mgs -dBATCH -dSAFER -sDEVICE=display  ../Recherche/colortransforms.pdf 
(does at least something)
commander@zombie:~/Projekte/Bücher/friedhofsengel/Tools/Multitone/Code$ ./dxmain.py -dBATCH -dSAFER -sDEVICE=display  ../Recherche/colortransforms.pdf 

"-dEPSFitPage" will blow up the eps to fit into the page
"-dEPSCrop" will crop the page to have the size of the eps

"-dTextAlphaBits=4" Antialiasing for text
"-dGraphicsAlphaBits=4" Antialiasing for graphics content

These options control the use of subsample antialiasing. Their use is highly recommended for producing high quality rasterizations of the input files. The size of the subsampling box n should be 4 for optimum output, but smaller values can be used for faster rendering. Antialiasing is enabled separately for text and graphics content.

-rres
-r300 # 300 dpi for x and y
-r{resx}x{resy}
-r150x72
    This option sets the resolution of the output file in dots per inch. The default value if you don't specify this options is usually 72 dpi.


There is an option, to just output one separation when DISPLAY_COLORS_SEPARATION is used, the following would only show Cyan
maybe this can be useful, however, it doesnt work with DISPLAY_COLORS_RGB where it may be best when it comes to colormanagement one day


./dxmain.py -dBATCH -dSAFER -sDEVICE=display  -dTextAlphaBits=4 << /SeparationColorNames [ /Cyan /Magenta /Yellow /Black (PANTONE 802 C) ] /SeparationOrder [ /Cyan ] >> setpagedevice" -f ~/Bürokratie/Rechnungen\ 2013/2013-0001-Compuccino.pdf

Since we will create the eps files ourselves, that might be a good point to include/exclude separationis.  Although that might get slow.
Ghosscript has ICC options, too, lets hope these will be of use.
